                    <span>As most of the reviews suggest, it is a great book and I highly recommend you to buy it. 
<br />
<br />There is a cheaper alternative to buying this though. Search for The Applied Microsoft .NET Framework Programming in C# Collection by the same author (Jeffrey Richter). That edition contains this book with lots of additional materials (CDs, Class Library posters etc) and surprisingly its MUCH cheaper than buying this by itself.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This is the 'Gold Standard' for other .NET Books I believe</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
